      "line": 64,
      "description": "In the `add` method, there's no check for null `rhs`. This could lead to a `NullPointerException` if `rhs` is null. Add a null check at the beginning of the method."
    },
    {
      "line": 74,
      "description": "In the `conjugate` method, there's no check for infinite real part. If the real part is infinite and the imaginary part is not NaN, the returned value should have an infinite real part of the same sign. Update the return statement to handle this case."
    },
    {
      "line": 96,
      "description": "In the `abs` method, there's no check for division by zero when calculating `q`. If the imaginary part is zero and the real part is not, `q` will be NaN, leading to incorrect results. Add a check for this case and return Double.POSITIVE_INFINITY if the real part is not zero."
    }
  ]
